","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"7237","uuid":"1d3873ee-776d-493e-8fd0-42db60d82b5a","stig_uuid":"5694459a-d227-4512-9afd-44c08c2a0979","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Ubuntu2004_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 68825488F2F17BED7F51C22EDDD0F2E4965E8BED\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'The Ubuntu operating system must generate audit records for successful/unsuccessful uses of the chacl command.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Ubuntu 20.04 LTS host."},{"group_id_src":"V-238285","group_tree":[{"id":"V-238285","title":"SRG-OS-000064-GPOS-00033","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-238285","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000064-GPOS-00033","rule_id_src":"SV-238285r958446_rule","rule_id":"SV-238285","rule_version":"UBTU-20-010169","rule_title":"The Ubuntu operating system must generate audit records for the use and modification of the tallylog file.","fix_text":"Configure the audit system to generate an audit event for any successful/unsuccessful modifications to the \"tallylog\" file.  \n \nAdd or update the following rules in the \"/etc/audit/rules.d/stig.rules\" file: \n \n-w /var/log/tallylog -p wa -k logins \n   \nTo reload the rules file, issue the following command: \n \n$ sudo augenrules --load","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the Ubuntu operating system generates an audit record upon successful/unsuccessful modifications to the \"tallylog\" file. \n \nCheck the currently configured audit rules with the following command: \n \n$ sudo auditctl -l | grep tallylog \n \n-w /var/log/tallylog -p wa -k logins \n \nIf the command does not return a line that matches the example or the line is commented out, this is a finding. \n \nNote: The \"-k\" allows for specifying an arbitrary identifier, and the string after it does not need to match the example output above.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Canonical_Ubuntu_20.04_LTS_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without generating audit records that are specific to the security and mission needs of the organization, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one. \n \nAudit records can be generated from various components within the information system (e.g., module or policy filter).\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000064-GPOS-00033, SRG-OS-000470-GPOS-00214, SRG-OS-000473-GPOS-00218","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"9932","uuid":"6bba6c28-f1a4-42c8-8d71-cb281457c88d","stig_uuid":"5694459a-d227-4512-9afd-44c08c2a0979","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-Ubuntu2004_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A721AE9CAAA22891C3FB375F220403F2B5D6AD05\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Ubuntu operating system must generate audit records for the use and modification of the tallylog file.' matches the expected value on the Ubuntu 20.04 LTS host."},{"group_id_src":"V-238286","group_tree":[{"id":"V-238286","title":"SRG-OS-000064-GPOS-00033","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-238286","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000064-GPOS-00033","rule_id_src":"SV-238286r958446_rule","rule_id":"SV-238286","rule_version":"UBTU-20-010170","rule_title":"The Ubuntu operating system must generate audit records for the use and modification of faillog file.","fix_text":"Configure the audit system to generate an audit event for any successful/unsuccessful modif